==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triglyph
<hw>Tri"glyph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>triglyphus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ (see <er>Tri-</er>) + <?/ to carve:
cf. F. <ets>triglyphe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>An ornament
in the frieze of the Doric order, repeated at equal intervals. Each
triglyph consists of a rectangular tablet, slightly projecting, and
divided nearly to the top by two parallel and perpendicular gutters, or
channels, called <xex>glyphs</xex>, into three parts, or spaces, called
<xex>femora</xex>. A half channel, or glyph, is also cut upon each of
the perpendicular edges of the tablet. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Entablature</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

